<h2 style="color:#908fa5">The Use of Gems</h2>
<p style="color:white">Gemstones are a key element in jewelry making, often used as stunning centerpieces in rings, necklaces, and earrings. Popular gems like diamonds, sapphires, and emeralds add elegance and value to each piece. Smaller gems can serve as accent stones, enhancing the overall design with extra sparkle. Whether as bold pendants or intricate settings, gemstones bring color, brilliance, and uniqueness to jewelry creations.</p>
